  "prompt": "What does \"ight\" mean?",
  "response": "\"Ight\" is a slang term that is short for \"alright\" or \"all right.\" It is often used in informal conversations, particularly in text messages or on social media, to indicate agreement, acknowledgment, or that everything is okay. For example:\n\n- \"You coming to the party tonight?\"  \n- \"Ight, I\u2019ll be there.\"\n\nIt\u2019s a casual and quick way to express assent or understanding.",
